    "body": "Problem:\r\n\r\n`%=` is documented as a separation point between alignment sections, but it was ignored inside fixed-width statusline item groups such as:\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n%20(foo%=bar%)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis also affected `rulerformat` when the ruler was rendered inside the statusline:\r\n\r\n```vim\r\nset ruler\r\nset laststatus=2\r\nset rulerformat=%20(%l,%c%V%=%P%m%)\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn that case the left and right parts were rendered without the expected spacing.\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\n\r\n- Preserve the leading fixed-width group in `rulerformat` when it is rendered as part of the statusline.\r\n- Handle `%=` locally inside fixed-width groups.\r\n- Prevent separators inside groups from being processed again as top-level separators.\r\n- Add a regression test for `%=` inside a fixed-width group.\r\n\r\nTest:\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nVIMRUNTIME=\"$PWD/runtime\" TEST_FILE=test/functional/ui/statusline_spec.lua make functionaltest\r\n```\r\n\r\nFixes #39984\r\n\r\nThis PR is AI Assisted",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
