            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`spaces_to_add` is a character count , but you're using it directly as a byte offset in `STRMOVE`. ",
            "commit_id": "36830539ba5777814f157893fda39c06b34042e5",
            "created_at": "2026-05-25T04:57:59Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -1118,6 +1120,56 @@ int build_stl_str_hl(win_T *wp, char *out, size_t outlen, char *fmt, OptIndex op\n         }\n       }\n \n+      // Handle %= inside a fixed-width group.\n+      //\n+      // A top-level %= is handled later, using the full statusline width.\n+      // For a group such as %20(foo%=bar%), the separator should only fill\n+      // the group's own width.\n+      int group_separators = 0;\n+      for (int idx = stl_groupitems[groupdepth] + 1; idx < curitem; idx++) {\n+        if (stl_items[idx].type == Separate) {\n+          group_separators++;\n+        }\n+      }\n+\n+      if (group_separators > 0) {\n+        int min_group_width = abs(stl_items[stl_groupitems[groupdepth]].minwid);\n+        int spaces_to_add = min_group_width - (int)group_len;\n+\n+        if (spaces_to_add > 0) {\n+          for (int idx = stl_groupitems[groupdepth] + 1; idx < curitem; idx++) {\n+            if (stl_items[idx].type != Separate) {\n+              continue;\n+            }\n+\n+            char *start = stl_items[idx].start;\n+            STRMOVE(start + spaces_to_add, start);",
